  "prompts": [
    {
      "name": "planning",
      "accept": [
        "Actionable implementation steps with clear deliverables",
        "Scope estimated with complexity assessment",
        "Dependencies and risks identified",
        "Test strategy covers requirements",
        "All invariants respected in the plan"
      ],
      "params": [
        {
          "name": "complexity",
          "param_type": "enum",
          "values": [
            "small",
            "medium",
            "large"
          ],
          "required": false,
          "default": null,
          "description": "Expected implementation complexity"
        }
      ],
      "outcomes": [
        {
          "name": "plan_complete",
          "target": "ready_for_plan_review",
          "is_success": true
        },
        {
          "name": "insufficient_context",
          "target": "ready_for_planning",
          "is_success": false
        },
        {
          "name": "out_of_scope",
          "target": "ready_for_planning",
          "is_success": false
        },
        {
          "name": "blocked_by_dependency",
          "target": "blocked",
          "is_success": false
        }
      ],
      "body": "# Planning\n\nBreak the knot into actionable implementation steps.\n\n## Invariant Adherence\n\n- If the knot has invariants, read and understand each one before planning.\n- Every step in the plan must respect all invariant conditions.\n\n## Actions\n\n1. Analyze the knot requirements and constraints\n2. Draft an implementation plan with steps, file changes, and test strategy\n3. Estimate complexity and identify risks\n4. Write the plan as a knot note\n\n## Output\n\n- Detailed implementation plan attached as a knot note\n- Hierarchy of knots created\n- Handoff capsule summarizing the plan",
      "body_params": []
    },
    {
      "name": "plan_review",
      "accept": [
        "Plan is complete, correct, and feasible",
        "Test strategy covers requirements",
        "No security, performance, or maintainability concerns",
        "All invariants respected"
      ],
      "params": [],
      "outcomes": [
        {
          "name": "approved",
          "target": "ready_for_implementation",
          "is_success": true
        },
        {
          "name": "plan_flawed",
          "target": "ready_for_planning",
          "is_success": false
        },
        {
          "name": "requirements_changed",
          "target": "ready_for_planning",
          "is_success": false
        },
        {
          "name": "blocked_by_dependency",
          "target": "blocked",
          "is_success": false
        }
      ],
      "body": "# Plan Review\n\nReview the implementation plan for completeness, correctness, and feasibility.\n\n## Actions\n\n1. Review the plan for completeness, correctness, and feasibility\n2. Verify the plan respects all knot invariants\n3. Verify test strategy covers requirements\n4. Approve or request revisions",
      "body_params": []
    },
    {
      "name": "implementation",
      "accept": [
        "Working implementation on feature branch",
        "All tests passing with coverage threshold met",
        "All invariants respected in the implementation",
        "Commits tagged on the knot"
      ],
      "params": [
        {
          "name": "output",
          "param_type": "enum",
          "values": [
            "remote_main",
            "pr",
            "branch",
            "live_deployment"
          ],
          "required": true,
          "default": null,
          "description": null
        }
      ],
      "outcomes": [
        {
          "name": "implementation_complete",
          "target": "ready_for_implementation_review",
          "is_success": true
        },
        {
          "name": "blocked_by_dependency",
          "target": "blocked",
          "is_success": false
        },
        {
          "name": "implementation_infeasible",
          "target": "ready_for_planning",
          "is_success": false
        },
        {
          "name": "merge_conflict",
          "target": "ready_for_implementation",
          "is_success": false
        }
      ],
      "body": "# Implementation\n\nImplement the approved plan on a feature branch.\n\n## Actions\n\n1. Create a feature branch from main in a worktree\n2. Implement changes following the plan while respecting all invariants\n3. Write tests for all new behavior\n4. Commit and push the feature branch\n5. Make the implementation artifact explicit for the profile output mode:\n   `{{ output }}` = `remote_main` means the review target is the pushed\n   feature branch itself, so leave the result ready for direct branch\n   review.\n   `{{ output }}` = `pr` means the review target is a pull request, so\n   open or update the PR for the feature branch.\n   `{{ output }}` = `branch` means push the feature branch to remote;\n   the branch itself is the deliverable (no merge to main expected).\n   `{{ output }}` = `live_deployment` means the review target is a\n   deployment artifact, so prepare the implementation for deployment.\n\n## Output\n\nThe expected output artifact is `{{ output }}`:\n- **remote_main**: a feature branch pushed to remote for direct branch review\n- **pr**: a pull request opened or updated from the feature branch\n- **branch**: a feature branch pushed to remote as the final deliverable\n- **live_deployment**: implementation ready for deployment to production",
      "body_params": [
        "output"
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "implementation_review",
      "accept": [
        "Code matches knot description and acceptance criteria",
        "All invariants respected in the implementation",
        "Tests cover required behavior",
        "All sanity gates pass",
        "No security issues or regressions"
      ],
      "params": [
        {
          "name": "output",
          "param_type": "enum",
          "values": [
            "remote_main",
            "pr",
            "branch",
            "live_deployment"
          ],
          "required": true,
          "default": null,
          "description": null
        }
      ],
      "outcomes": [
        {
          "name": "approved",
          "target": "ready_for_shipment",
          "is_success": true
        },
        {
          "name": "changes_requested",
          "target": "ready_for_implementation",
          "is_success": false
        },
        {
          "name": "architecture_concern",
          "target": "ready_for_implementation",
          "is_success": false
        },
        {
          "name": "critical_issues",
          "target": "ready_for_implementation",
          "is_success": false
        }
      ],
      "body": "# Implementation Review\n\nReview the implementation against the knot description and acceptance criteria.\n\n## Actions\n\n1. Review code changes against the knot description and acceptance criteria\n2. Verify the implementation respects all knot invariants\n3. Verify tests cover the required behavior\n4. Use the correct review target for the profile output mode:\n   `{{ output }}` = `remote_main` means review the implementation branch\n   directly using the branch diff, status, and test results.\n   `{{ output }}` = `pr` means review the pull request itself, including\n   the PR diff, status, and metadata.\n   `{{ output }}` = `branch` means review the pushed branch as the final\n   deliverable, using the branch diff and test results.\n   `{{ output }}` = `live_deployment` means review the implementation\n   for deployment readiness, including infrastructure and rollback plan.\n5. Approve or request changes",
      "body_params": [
        "output"
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "shipment",
      "accept": [
        "Code merged and pushed to main",
        "CI green on remote",
        "All invariants still hold after merge",
        "All commits tagged on the knot"
      ],
      "params": [
        {
          "name": "output",
          "param_type": "enum",
          "values": [
            "remote_main",
            "pr",
            "branch",
            "live_deployment"
          ],
          "required": true,
          "default": null,
          "description": null
        }
      ],
      "outcomes": [
        {
          "name": "shipment_complete",
          "target": "ready_for_shipment_review",
          "is_success": true
        },
        {
          "name": "merge_conflicts",
          "target": "ready_for_implementation",
          "is_success": false
        },
        {
          "name": "ci_failure",
          "target": "ready_for_implementation",
          "is_success": false
        },
        {
          "name": "release_blocked",
          "target": "blocked",
          "is_success": false
        }
      ],
      "body": "# Shipment\n\nPromote the approved implementation to its final destination. The\nimplementation has already been reviewed and approved — your job is to\nmerge, push, and verify, not to re-review or second-guess the work.\n\n## Locating the Implementation\n\nFind the feature branch by reading the knot metadata:\n1. Check `commit:` tags on the knot — these are the implementation\n   commit hashes.\n2. Read the most recent handoff capsules — they typically name the\n   branch (e.g., `worktree-<knot-id>-*`).\n3. Run `git branch -a --contains <tagged-commit>` to confirm which\n   branch holds the work.\n\nIf the tagged commits are already on main, shipment is already done —\nverify CI is green and advance. Do not roll back.\n\n## Actions\n\n1. Perform the shipment action that matches the profile output mode:\n   `{{ output }}` = `remote_main` means merge the feature branch to main.\n   `{{ output }}` = `pr` means merge the approved pull request instead of\n   performing a branch-only review flow.\n   `{{ output }}` = `branch` means the branch is the final artifact;\n   verify it is pushed and CI passes.\n   `{{ output }}` = `live_deployment` means merge to main and deploy to\n   the target environment.\n2. Push or verify the shipped result required by the output mode:\n   `{{ output }}` = `remote_main` means push main after the merge.\n   `{{ output }}` = `pr` means verify the merged PR produced the intended\n   main-branch result and that the remote reflects it.\n   `{{ output }}` = `branch` means verify the branch is on remote.\n   `{{ output }}` = `live_deployment` means verify the deployment\n   completed and the service is healthy.\n3. Verify CI passes on remote\n\n## Output\n\nThe expected output artifact is `{{ output }}`:\n- **remote_main**: code merged from the feature branch to main and\n  pushed to remote\n- **pr**: an approved pull request merged and reflected on main\n- **branch**: feature branch pushed to remote as the final deliverable\n- **live_deployment**: code merged, deployed, and verified healthy\n\n## When to Roll Back\n\nOnly roll back to `ready_for_implementation` when the merge itself\nfails (conflicts, CI red after merge). Finding unmerged commits is\nthe normal starting condition — that is what shipment is for.",
      "body_params": [
        "output"
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "shipment_review",
      "accept": [
        "Change is live on main branch",
        "Every commit tagged on the knot",
        "All invariants hold in shipped code",
        "CI/CD pipeline completed successfully",
        "No regressions in dependent systems"
      ],
      "params": [
        {
          "name": "output",
          "param_type": "enum",
          "values": [
            "remote_main",
            "pr",
            "branch",
            "live_deployment"
          ],
          "required": true,
          "default": null,
          "description": null
        }
      ],
      "outcomes": [
        {
          "name": "approved",
          "target": "shipped",
          "is_success": true
        },
        {
          "name": "approved_already_merged",
          "target": "shipped",
          "is_success": true
        },
        {
          "name": "needs_revision",
          "target": "ready_for_implementation",
          "is_success": false
        },
        {
          "name": "critical_regression",
          "target": "ready_for_implementation",
          "is_success": false
        },
